## Data Flow Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph UI["UI Screens"]
        LP[LoginPage]
        RP[RegisterPage]
        UD[UserDashboard]
        EL[ExamListPage]
        ET[ExamTakingPage]
        QP[QuestPage]
        AS[AvatarStorePage]
        AD[AdminDashboard]
        CE[CreateExamPage]
        EM[ExamMgmtPage]
        CQ[CreateQuestionsPage]
        US[UploadSkinPage]
    end

    subgraph State["BLoCs / Cubits"]
        AB[AuthBloc]
        EB[ExamBloc]
        ATB[AttemptBloc]
        QB[QuestBloc]
        ASC[AdminStatsCubit]
    end

    subgraph Data["Repositories"]
        AR[AuthRepositoryImpl]
        UR[UserRepository]
        ER[ExamRepository]
        ATR[AttemptRepository]
        QR[QuestRepository]
        SR[StoreRepository]
    end

    subgraph Firebase["Firebase"]
        FA[FirebaseAuth]
        FF[Firestore]
        FS[Storage]
    end

    LP & RP --> AB --> AR --> FA & FF
    UD --> AB
    EL --> EB --> ER --> FF & FS
    ET --> ATB --> ATR & ER
    QP --> QB --> QR --> FF
    AS -->|direct call| SR & UR
    AD --> ASC --> ER & UR
    CE & EM & CQ --> ER
    US --> SR --> FF & FS
```

---

## Authentication Flows

### Email Sign-Up Flow
1. `LoginPage` → dispatches `AuthCreateAccountRequested` → **AuthBloc**
2. **AuthBloc** → calls `createAccountWithEmail()` → **AuthRepositoryImpl**
3. **AuthRepositoryImpl** → calls `createAccountWithEmail()` → **AuthRemoteDataSource** → **FirebaseAuth**
4. Checks `admin_whitelist/{email}` document existence → determines role
5. Writes user profile to `users/{uid}` with role, xp=0, level=1, coins=0
6. Returns `UserEntity` → **AuthBloc** emits `AuthAuthenticated`
7. **AppRouter** detects auth state change → redirects to dashboard

### Google/Apple Sign-In Flow
1. OAuth flow via GoogleSignIn / SignInWithApple SDK
2. Firebase `signInWithCredential()` with OAuth token
3. Check if `users/{uid}` doc exists:
   - **New user**: Create profile (check admin_whitelist for role)
   - **Existing user**: Update `lastLoginAt` only

---

## Missing Links Identified

> [!WARNING]
> ### 1. No StoreBloc/StoreCubit
> `AvatarStorePage` calls `StoreRepository` and `UserRepository` directly, bypassing the BLoC pattern used by every other feature. This breaks separation of concerns and makes the store harder to test.

> [!WARNING]
> ### 2. No DashboardBloc/DashboardCubit
> `UserDashboardPage` appears to rely on `AuthBloc`'s state for user data rather than having its own state management for fetching stats, recent attempts, or quest progress.

> [!WARNING]
> ### 3. Quest Completion → XP Pipeline Not Wired
> `QuestBloc` depends only on `QuestRepository`. There is no connection to `UserRepository.awardXp()`, meaning quest completion doesn't appear to automatically award XP or trigger level-ups. This pipeline would need to be manually orchestrated.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### 4. No Real-Time Listeners
> All Firestore reads use one-shot `.get()` calls. No `snapshots()` streams are used anywhere. This means:
> - UI won't auto-update if an admin changes data while a student is viewing it
> - Multi-device sync won't work without manual refresh
> - The AvatarStorePage already has a "Retry/Refresh" workaround for this

